<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1082">
Let $\sigma(n)$ denote the sum of divisors of an integer $n$. For example, $\sigma(12)=1+2+3+4+6+12=28$.<br />
<br />
Your task is to calculate the sum $\sum_{i=1}^n \sigma(i)$ modulo $10^9+7$.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print $\sum_{i=1}^n \sigma(i)$ modulo $10^9+7$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 10^{12}$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>21</code>    </div>
